{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870436770,"sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","part":{"id":"prt_d7a20605f001VZ5NitdwDyMczh","messageID":"msg_d7a2045e80018XbjE7LEx1K7S4","sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_efa2d77d694447d4b7fc84ef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI Build Command Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: BuildRuntime Implementation (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Update `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` - Add package imports\n18:   - Define imports: `logging`, `re`, `pathlib.Path`, `typing.Any, Dict, Optional`\n19:   - Import `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` from `agentcube.services.metadata_service`\n20:   - Import `DockerService` from `agentcube.services.docker_service`\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `BuildRuntime.__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` in `build_runtime.py`\n23:   - Initialize `self.verbose = verbose`\n24:   - Configure logging if verbose\n25:   - Initialize `self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)`\n26:   - Initialize `self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)`\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `BuildRuntime.build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `build_runtime.py`\n29:   - Log build start\n30:   - Load metadata from workspace\n31:   - Validate build prerequisites\n32:   - Store original version for rollback\n33:   - Increment version\n34:   - Try/except block for build with version rollback on failure\n35:   - Determine build mode (local vs cloud)\n36:   - Call `_build_local` or `_build_cloud`\n37:   - Update build metadata on success\n38:   - Return result dict\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `BuildRuntime._increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str` in `build_runtime.py`\n41:   - Parse semver version using regex\n42:   - Handle patch increment (1.2.3 → 1.2.4)\n43:   - Handle pre-release versions (1.0.0-alpha.1 → 1.0.0-alpha.2)\n44:   - Handle non-semver fallback (v1.0 → v1.0.1)\n45:   - Handle missing version (default to 0.1.0)\n46:   - Save updated metadata\n47:   - Log and return new version\n48: \n49: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None` in `build_runtime.py`\n50:   - Check Dockerfile exists in workspace\n51:   - Raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")` if missing\n52:   - Call `docker_service.check_docker_available()`\n53:   - Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if unavailable\n54: \n55: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `build_runtime.py`\n56:   - Construct dockerfile_path\n57:   - Construct image_name with version\n58:   - Extract proxy from options\n59:   - Build build_args dict with HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY if proxy provided\n60:   - Call `docker_service.build_image()` with required params\n61:   - Add image_name to result\n62:   - Return result dict\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Implement `BuildRuntime._build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `build_runtime.py`\n65:   - Extract cloud_provider from options (default: \"huawei\")\n66:   - Validate cloud provider is supported\n67:   - Raise `ValueError(f\"Unsupported cloud provider: {cloud_provider}\")` if not\n68:   - Log cloud build start\n69:   - Return placeholder result dict with cloud-specific image_name\n70: \n71: - [ ] **TASK-008**: Implement `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, build_result: Dict[str, str])` in `build_runtime.py`\n72:   - Initialize metadata.image dict if None\n73:   - Update metadata.image with build_result\n74:   - Save metadata via metadata_service\n75: \n76: ### Phase 2: DockerService Implementation (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n77: \n78: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Update `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` - Add package imports\n79:   - Define imports: `logging`, `time`, `pathlib.Path`, `typing.Any, Dict, Optional`\n80:   - Import `docker` from docker package\n81:   - Import `DockerException` from docker.errors\n82: \n83: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `DockerService.__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` in `docker_service.py`\n84:   - Initialize `self.verbose = verbose`\n85:   - Configure logging if verbose\n86:   - Initialize `self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `DockerService.client` property in `docker_service.py`\n89:   - Create docker client via `docker.from_env()` if None\n90:   - Return client\n91: \n92: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `DockerService.check_docker_available(self) -> bool` in `docker_service.py`\n93:   - Try to ping docker client\n94:   - Return True on success\n95:   - Catch DockerException, log warning, return False\n96: \n97: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `DockerService.build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]` in `docker_service.py`\n98:   - Check docker availability first\n99:   - Log build start\n100:   - Call `client.images.build()` with path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs, rm, forcerm\n101:   - Get image info via `get_image_info()`\n102:   - Add build_time to result\n103:   - Return result dict\n104:   - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `DockerService.get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` in `docker_service.py`\n107:   - Get image via `client.images.get()`\n108:   - Extract image_id from attrs[\"Id\"]\n109:   - Extract size from attrs[\"Size\"]\n110:   - Format size using `_format_size()`\n111:   - Return dict with image_name, image_id, image_size, size_bytes\n112:   - Catch DockerException and return empty dict\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `DockerService._format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str` in `docker_service.py`\n115:   - Convert bytes to human-readable format\n116:   - Iterate through [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]\n117:   - Return formatted string (e.g., \"125.50 MB\")\n118: \n119: - [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `DockerService.push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]` in `docker_service.py`\n120:   - Check docker availability\n121:   - Tag image if registry_url provided\n122:   - Login if username and password provided\n123:   - Push image with streaming\n124:   - Check for errors in push logs\n125:   - Log progress if verbose\n126:   - Return dict with pushed_image, push_time\n127:   - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n128: \n129: - [ ] **TASK-018**: Implement `DockerService._docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None` in `docker_service.py`\n130:   - Call `client.login()` with credentials\n131:   - Log success\n132:   - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n133: \n134: - [ ] **TASK-019**: Implement `DockerService._tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None` in `docker_service.py`\n135:   - Get source image\n136:   - Call `image.tag()` with target_image\n137:   - Log success\n138:   - Catch DockerException and raise RuntimeError\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `DockerService.remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool` in `docker_service.py`\n141:   - Call `client.images.remove()` with force=True\n142:   - Log success\n143:   - Return True\n144:   - Catch DockerException, log warning, return False\n145: \n146: ### Phase 3: CLI Build Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Update `agentcube/cli/main.py` - Import BuildRuntime\n149:   - Add import: `from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `build()` command in `main.py` with Typer decorator\n152:   - Define function with `@app.command()` decorator\n153:   - Accept `workspace` option (-f, --workspace, default \".\")\n154:   - Accept `proxy` option (-p, --proxy, Optional[str])\n155:   - Accept `cloud_provider` option (--cloud-provider, Optional[str])\n156:   - Accept `output` option (--output, Optional[str])\n157:   - Accept `verbose` option (--verbose, bool, default False)\n158:   - Add docstring for command help\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `build()` command body in `main.py`\n161:   - Configure logging if verbose\n162:   - Instantiate `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)`\n163:   - Resolve workspace_path\n164:   - Show progress spinner with Rich\n165:   - Build options dict with proxy, cloud_provider, output\n166:   - Call `runtime.build(workspace_path, **options)`\n167:   - Update progress on completion\n168:   - Print success message with image_name, image_id, image_size\n169:   - Handle errors with `_handle_error()`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Update `_handle_error()` to support build command\n172:   - Ensure error messages include command context\n173:   - Print traceback if verbose\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Add build time to success output\n176:   - Print `build_time` from result if available\n177: \n178: - [ ] **TASK-035**: Add next step guidance after build success\n179:   - Suggest `agentcube publish` command with appropriate flags\n180: \n181: ### Phase 4: Cloud Provider Support (`agentcube/services/cloud_providers/`)\n182: \n183: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/__init__.py`\n184:   - Package marker with docstring\n185:   - Export provider classes\n186: \n187: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Create `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/base.py`\n188:   - Define `CloudProvider` abstract base class\n189:   - Define abstract methods: `build_image()`, `check_credentials()`, `get_build_status()`\n190:   - Define common constants and types\n191: \n192: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Create `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/huawei.py`\n193:   - Implement `HuaweiCloudProvider` class extending `CloudProvider`\n194:   - Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n195:   - Implement `build_image()` - trigger Huawei Cloud Container Registry build\n196:   - Implement `check_credentials()` - validate Huawei Cloud credentials\n197:   - Implement `get_build_status()` - poll build status\n198:   - Handle timeout (default 600s)\n199:   - Raise `TimeoutError(\"Cloud build exceeded timeout\")` on timeout\n200: \n201: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement cloud provider factory in `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/__init__.py`\n202:   - Create `get_provider(name: str, verbose: bool = False) -> CloudProvider`\n203:   - Map provider names to classes\n204:   - Raise `ValueError(f\"Unsupported cloud provider: {name}\")` for unknown providers\n205: \n206: ### Phase 5: Proxy Configuration Support\n207: \n208: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Add proxy environment variable fallback in `build_runtime.py`\n209:   - Check for `HTTP_PROXY` or `HTTPS_PROXY` env vars if no `-p` flag\n210:   - Use env var as proxy value\n211: \n212: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Document proxy support for pip installs in `_build_local()`\n213:   - Add comment for future enhancement: pass proxy to pip via build args\n214: \n215: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Document proxy support for maven builds in `_build_local()`