ut` in `test_build_command.py`\n378:   - Run build in workspace without Dockerfile\n379:   - Verify error message displayed\n380:   - Verify exit code is 1\n381: \n382: ### Phase 9: Integration Tests\n383: \n384: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n385:   - Define integration test imports\n386: \n387: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Implement `test_build_hello_agent_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n388:   - Use examples/hello-agent workspace\n389:   - Run full pack → build flow\n390:   - Verify Docker image created\n391:   - Verify image can be inspected\n392: \n393: - [ ] **TEST-042**: Implement `test_build_math_agent_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n394:   - Use examples/math-agent workspace\n395:   - Run full pack → build flow\n396:   - Verify Docker image created with correct name/tag\n397: \n398: - [ ] **TEST-043**: Implement `test_build_with_proxy_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n399:   - Start test proxy server\n400:   - Run build with proxy\n401:   - Verify proxy used for dependency resolution (if testable)\n402: \n403: - [ ] **TEST-044**: Implement `test_build_version_persists_integration` in `test_build_integration.py`\n404:   - Build agent twice\n405:   - Verify version incremented each time\n406:   - Verify metadata reflects final version\n407: \n408: ### Phase 10: Documentation\n409: \n410: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add docstrings to BuildRuntime class and all methods\n411:   - Include parameter descriptions\n412:   - Include return value descriptions\n413:   - Include error conditions\n414: \n415: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add docstrings to DockerService class and all methods\n416:   - Include parameter descriptions\n417:   - Include return value descriptions\n418:   - Include error conditions\n419: \n420: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add docstrings to CloudProvider classes\n421:   - Document cloud provider interface\n422:   - Document Huawei Cloud implementation\n423: \n424: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `cmd/cli/README.md`\n425:   - Document build command\n426:   - Include usage examples\n427:   - Document cloud provider options\n428:   - Document proxy configuration\n429: \n430: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/README.md` section for build\n431:   - Document building example agents\n432:   - Include common troubleshooting\n433: \n434: ### Phase 11: Error Codes and Exit Handling\n435: \n436: - [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement error exit codes in `build()` command\n437:   - Exit code 1 for all errors\n438:   - Ensure typer.Exit(1) raised on errors\n439: \n440: - [ ] **TASK-081**: Document error codes\n441:   - Docker unavailable → 1\n442:   - Missing Dockerfile → 1\n443:   - Invalid cloud provider → 1\n444:   - Build failure → 1\n445:   - Cloud build timeout → 1\n446:   - Version increment failure → 1\n447: \n448: ### Phase 12: Coverage Verification\n449: \n450: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n451:   - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing tests/`\n452:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n453:   - Verify build_runtime.py, docker_service.py, main.py build command all covered\n454:   - Verify each .py file has corresponding test_*.py file\n455:   - Verify main logic paths covered\n456: \n457: ## Acceptance Criteria\n458: \n459: - [ ] `agentcube build` command registered and accessible\n460: - [ ] Build command accepts all specified options (-f, -p, --cloud-provider, --output, --verbose)\n461: - [ ] Default workspace resolves to current directory\n462: - [ ] Custom workspace path works (absolute and relative)\n463: - [ ] Proxy configuration passed to build\n464: - [ ] Cloud provider selection overrides to cloud mode\n465: - [ ] Output path for build artifacts supported\n466: - [ ] Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging\n467: - [ ] BuildRuntime instantiated with verbose flag\n468: - [ ] BuildRuntime.build() called with options dict\n469: - [ ] Exceptions handled with _handle_error()\n470: - [ ] Success message displayed with image details\n471: - [ ] Build mode resolution: local default, cloud with --cloud-provider\n472: - [ ] Cloud mode requires cloud provider name\n473: - [ ] Docker availability check before local build\n474: - [ ] Docker not available raises RuntimeError\n475: - [ ] DockerService.build_image() called with correct params\n476: - [ ] Image tagging convention: {agent_name}:{version}\n477: - [ ] Fallback tag: {agent_name}:latest when no version\n478: - [ ] Version increment: patch (1.2.3 → 1.2.4)\n479: - [ ] Pre-release version handling (1.0.0-alpha.1 → 1.0.0-alpha.2)\n480: - [ ] Version revert on build failure\n481: - [ ] Version string fallback for non-semver\n482: - [ ] Cloud build triggers cloud provider\n483: - [ ] Unsupported cloud provider raises ValueError\n484: - [ ] Dockerfile existence check\n485: - [ ] Missing Dockerfile raises ValueError\n486: - [ ] Metadata validation\n487: - [ ] Image name validation/sanitization\n488: - [ ] Build success output formatted with Rich\n489: - [ ] Build result updates agent_metadata.yaml\n490: - [ ] Verbose mode streams build logs\n491: - [ ] Next step guidance suggests publish command\n492: - [ ] Proxy from CLI flag or environment variable\n493: - [ ] Error exit codes all return 1\n494: - [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n495: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n496: - [ ] All error messages match spec\n497: \n498: ## Dependencies\n499: \n500: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n501: |------------|--------|-------|\n502: | `typer[all]` | External (>=0.9.0) | CLI framework |\n503: | `pydantic` | External (>=2.0.0) | Data validation |\n504: | `docker` | External (>=6.0.0) | Docker SDK |\n505: | `rich` | External (>=13.0.0) | Output formatting |\n506: | `semver` | External (>=3.0.0) | Version parsing |\n507: | `pyyaml` | External (>=6.0) | Metadata handling |\n508: | `pytest` | External (>=7.4.0) | Testing framework |\n509: | `pytest-asyncio` | External (>=0.21.0) | Async test support |\n510: | `pytest-cov` | External (>=4.1.0) | Coverage reporting |\n511: | `pytest-mock` | External (>=3.11.0) | Mocking utilities |\n512: | delta-spec-ar-021.md | Internal | Build command specification |\n513: | cli-toolkit/spec.md | Internal | CLI specification |\n514: | AR-020 (CLI pack command) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n515: \n516: ## Implementation Order\n517: \n518: ```\n519: TASK-001 → TASK-009 (BuildRuntime core)\n520:     ↓\n521: TASK-010 → TASK-020 (DockerService)\n522:     ↓\n523: TASK-030 → TASK-035 (CLI build command)\n524:     ↓\n525: TASK-040 → TASK-043 (Cloud providers)\n526:     ↓\n527: TASK-050 → TASK-052 (Proxy support)\n528:     ↓\n529: TASK-060 → TASK-061 (Build validation)\n530:     ↓\n531: TASK-070 → TASK-072 (Output/reporting)\n532:     ↓\n533: TASK-080 → TASK-081 (Error codes)\n534:     ↓\n535: TEST-001 → TEST-029 (Unit tests)\n536:     ↓\n537: TEST-030 → TEST-038 (CLI command tests)\n538:     ↓\n539: TEST-040 → TEST-044 (Integration tests)\n540:     ↓\n541: DOC-001 → DOC-005 (Documentation)\n542:     ↓\n543: COV-001 (Coverage verification)\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ## File Structure\n547: \n548: ```\n549: cmd/cli/\n550: ├── agentcube/\n551: │   ├── cli/\n552: │   │   └── main.py (updated with build command)\n553: │   ├── runtime/\n554: │   │   └── build_runtime.py (implemented)\n555: │   ├── services/\n556: │   │   ├── docker_service.py (implemented)\n557: │   │   └── cloud_providers/\n558: │   │       ├── __init__.py\n559: │   │       ├── base.py\n560: │   │       └── huawei.py\n561: │   └── models/\n562: │       └── pack_models.py (from AR-020)\n563: └── tests/\n564:     ├── test_build_runtime.py\n565:     ├── test_docker_service.py\n566:     ├── test_build_command.py\n567:     └── test_build_integration.py\n568: ```\n569: \n570: ## Command Reference\n571: \n572: ### build Command\n573: \n574: ```bash\n575: kubectl-agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n576: \n577: Options:\n578:   -f, --workspace PATH          Path to agent workspace directory [default: .]\n579:   -p, --proxy TEXT              Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n580:   --cloud-provider TEXT         Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n581:   --output PATH                 Output path for build artifacts\n582:   --verbose                     Enable detailed logging\n583:   --help                        Show this message and exit\n584: ```\n585: \n586: ### Example Usage\n587: \n588: ```bash\n589: # Build with defaults (local Docker build)\n590: kubectl-agentcube build -f /path/to/agent\n591: \n592: # Build with proxy\n593: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent -p http://proxy.company.com:8080\n594: \n595: # Build in cloud (Huawei Cloud)\n596: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --cloud-provider huawei\n597: \n598: # Build with custom output\n599: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --output /tmp/build-output\n600: \n601: # Build with verbose logging\n602: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --verbose\n603: \n604: # Full workflow: pack → build → publish\n605: kubectl-agentcube pack -f ./my-agent\n606: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent\n607: kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent\n608: ```\n609: \n610: ## Testing Strategy\n611: \n612: ### Unit Tests\n613: \n614: 1. **BuildRuntime Tests**: Validate build logic, version increment/rollback, mode resolution\n615: 2. **DockerService Tests**: Validate Docker operations, image building, pushing\n616: 3. **CLI Command Tests**: Validate CLI option parsing, error handling, output formatting\n617: \n618: ### Integration Tests\n619: \n620: 1. **test_build_hello_agent_integration**: Full pack → build flow with hello-agent\n621: 2. **test_build_math_agent_integration**: Full pack → build flow with math-agent\n622: 3. **test_build_with_proxy_integration**: Build with proxy configuration\n623: 4. **test_build_version_persists_integration**: Version increment across builds\n624: \n625: ### Test Fixtures\n626: \n627: - `python_workspace_with_dockerfile/`: Python workspace with Dockerfile, main.py, requirements.txt, agent_metadata.yaml\n628: - `python_workspace_no_dockerfile/`: Python workspace without Dockerfile\n629: - `mock_docker_client`: Mocked Docker client for unit tests\n630: \n631: ## Security Considerations\n632: \n633: - [ ] **SEC-001**: Verify Docker daemon connection uses secure socket\n634: - [ ] **SEC-002**: Verify proxy credentials not logged in verbose mode\n635: - [ ] **SEC-003**: Verify cloud provider credentials handled securely\n636: - [ ] **SEC-004**: Verify error messages don't leak sensitive information\n637: - [ ] **SEC-005**: Verify image names sanitized to prevent injection attacks\n638: \n639: ## Open Questions (from spec)\n640: \n641: 1. Should build command support `--tag` override for custom image tags? (Future enhancement)\n642: 2. Should multi-platform builds (`--platform`) be supported in initial release? (Future enhancement)\n643: 3. Should build cache options (`--no-cache`, `--cache-from`) be exposed? (Future enhancement)\n\n(End of file - total 643 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI Build Command Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: BuildRuntime Implementation (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Update `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` - Add package imports\n  - Define imports: `logging`, `re`, `pathlib.Path`, `typing.Any, Dict, Optional`\n  - Import `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` from `agentcube.services.metadata_service`\n  - Import `DockerService` from `agentcube.services.docker_service`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775870436737,"end":1775870436767}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870436786,"sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2050d6001QdvdQ6DQsres2I","messageID":"msg_d7a2045e80018XbjE7LEx1K7S4","sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0a1aafa44eb34a47895fd3a9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import logging\n4: import time\n5: from pathlib import Path\n6: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n7: \n8: import docker\n9: from docker.errors import DockerException\n10: \n11: \n12: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n13: \n14: \n15: class DockerService:\n16:     \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n17: \n18:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n19:         \"\"\"Initialize the Docker service.\"\"\"\n20:         self.verbose = verbose\n21:         if verbose:\n22:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n23:         self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n24: \n25:     @property\n26:     def client(self) -> docker.DockerClient:\n27:         \"\"\"Get or create Docker client.\"\"\"\n28:         if self._client is None:\n29:             self._client = docker.from_env()\n30:         return self._client\n31: \n32:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n33:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available and running.\"\"\"\n34:         try:\n35:             self.client.ping()\n36:             return True\n37:         except DockerException as e:\n38:             logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n39:             return False\n40: \n41:     def build_image(\n42:         self,\n43:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n44:         context_path: Path,\n45:         image_name: str,\n46:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n47:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n48:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n49:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n50:         if not self.check_docker_available():\n51:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n52: \n53:         logger.info(f\"Building image {image_name}:{tag} from {dockerfile_path}\")\n54:         full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n55: \n56:         try:\n57:             image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n58:                 path=str(context_path),\n59:                 dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n60:                 tag=full_image_name,\n61:                 buildargs=build_args,\n62:                 rm=True,\n63:                 forcerm=True,\n64:             )\n65: \n66:             image_info = self.get_image_info(full_image_name)\n67:             image_info[\"build_time\"] = time.time()\n68: \n69:             return image_info\n70: \n71:         except DockerException as e:\n72:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n73: \n74:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n75:         \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\"\"\"\n76:         try:\n77:             image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n78:             attrs = image.attrs\n79: \n80:             image_id = attrs[\"Id\"].split(\":\")[-1][:12]\n81:             size_bytes = attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)\n82: \n83:             return {\n84:                 \"image_name\": image_name,\n85:                 \"image_id\": image_id,\n86:                 \"image_size\": self._format_size(size_bytes),\n87:                 \"size_bytes\": size_bytes,\n88:             }\n89: \n90:         except DockerException as e:\n91:             logger.warning(f\"Failed to get image info for {image_name}: {e}\")\n92:             return {}\n93: \n94:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n95:         \"\"\"Format size in human-readable format.\"\"\"\n96:         for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]:\n97:             if size_bytes < 1024:\n98:                 return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} {unit}\"\n99:             size_bytes /= 1024\n100:         return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} TB\"\n101: \n102:     def push_image(\n103:         self,\n104:         image_name: str,\n105:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n107:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n108:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n109:         \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\"\"\"\n110:         if not self.check_docker_available():\n111:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n112: \n113:         target_image = image_name\n114:         if registry_url:\n115:             target_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n116:             self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target_image)\n117: \n118:         if username and password:\n119:             self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n120: \n121:         logger.info(f\"Pushing image {target_image}\")\n122: \n123:         try:\n124:             push_logs = self.client.images.push(target_image, stream=True, decode=True)\n125: \n126:             for line in push_logs:\n127:                 if \"error\" in line:\n128:                     raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push image: {line['error']}\")\n129:                 if self.verbose:\n130:                     logger.debug(f\"Push log: {line}\")\n131: \n132:             return {\n133:                 \"pushed_image\": target_image,\n134:                 \"push_time\": str(time.time()),\n135:             }\n136: \n137:         except DockerException as e:\n138:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push Docker image: {e}\") from e\n139: \n140:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n141:         \"\"\"Log in to Docker registry.\"\"\"\n142:         try:\n143:             self.client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry)\n144:             logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry or 'default'}\")\n145:         except DockerException as e:\n146:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to log in to Docker registry: {e}\") from e\n147: \n148:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n149:         \"\"\"Tag a Docker image.\"\"\"\n150:         try:\n151:             image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n152:             image.tag(target_image, force=True)\n153:             logger.info(f\"Tagged {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n154:         except DockerException as e:\n155:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to tag Docker image: {e}\") from e\n156: \n157:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n158:         \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\"\"\"\n159:         try:\n160:             self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=True)\n161:             logger.info(f\"Removed image {image_name}\")\n162:             return True\n163:         except DockerException as e:\n164:             logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n165:             return False\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nimport time\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nimport docker\nfrom docker.errors import DockerException\n\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the Docker service.\"\"\"\n        self.verbose = verbose","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py","time":{"start":1775870436726,"end":1775870436782}}}}
