{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775870451496,"sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","part":{"id":"prt_d7a209f25001PUlkAfbMQPNHVV","messageID":"msg_d7a20929b001B6zkCroJmq83TK","sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870530014,"sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","part":{"id":"prt_d7a20a2fa001Sy4JrpeXL8Q1L2","messageID":"msg_d7a20929b001B6zkCroJmq83TK","sessionID":"ses_285dfcd31ffedSzD5MieQiRrnX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d82d746625bf4bdf8b4a5ceb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","content":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Core DockerService Implementation ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Implement `DockerService.__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n  - Initialize `self.verbose = verbose`\n  - Configure logging if verbose\n  - Initialize `self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None`\n  - Try to create Docker client, handle Docker unavailable gracefully\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Service instantiates with/without verbose mode\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Implement `client` property\n  - Create Docker client via `docker.from_env()` if None\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` if Docker not available\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Returns valid Docker client\n\n- [x] **T1.3** Implement `check_docker_available(self) -> bool`\n  - Try to ping Docker client\n  - Return True on success, False on failure\n  - Handle `DockerException` and `APIError`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Returns True when Docker running, False otherwise\n\n- [x] **T1.4** Implement `build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]`\n  - Check Docker availability first\n  - Log build start\n  - Call `client.images.build()` with required params\n  - Track build time\n  - Get image info via `_get_image_info()`\n  - Add `build_time` to result dict\n  - Log build logs in verbose mode\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Returns dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n\n- [x] **T1.5** Implement `get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n  - Delegate to `_get_image_info()` internal method\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Returns complete image info dict\n\n- [x] **T1.6** Implement `_get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n  - Get image via `client.images.get()`\n  - Extract `image_id` from attrs[\"Id\"] (12 chars)\n  - Extract size from attrs[\"Size\"]\n  - Format size using `_format_size()`\n  - Return dict: `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `size_bytes`\n  - Handle `DockerException`, `APIError`, `KeyError`\n  - Return empty dict on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Returns correct structure or empty dict\n\n- [x] **T1.7** Implement `_format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str`\n  - Convert bytes to human-readable format\n  - Iterate through [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]\n  - Return formatted string (e.g., \"125.50 MB\")\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Formats all size ranges correctly\n\n- [x] **T1.8** Implement `push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]`\n  - Check Docker availability\n  - Tag image if registry_url provided\n  - Login if username and password provided\n  - Push image with streaming logs\n  - Track push time\n  - Check for errors in push logs\n  - Log progress in verbose mode\n  - Return dict with `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Returns pushed image name and duration\n\n- [x] **T1.9** Implement `_docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None`\n  - Call `client.login()` with credentials\n  - Use default registry URL if None\n  - Log success\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Logs in successfully with valid credentials\n\n- [x] **T1.10** Implement `_tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None`\n  - Get source image\n  - Call `image.tag()` with target_image\n  - Log success\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Tags image successfully\n\n- [x] **T1.11** Implement `remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool`\n  - Call `client.images.remove()` with force=True\n  - Log success\n  - Return True on success\n  - Handle `DockerException` and `APIError`, return False on failure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Removes image or returns False\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Error Handling Enhancement\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Add comprehensive docstrings to all public methods\n  - Document all parameters with types\n  - Document return value structure\n  - Document all exception conditions\n  - Follow Google/NumPy style conventions\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: `help(DockerService.method)` displays correctly\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Add type hints to all methods and return types\n  - Use `typing` module for complex types\n  - Ensure `from __future__ import annotations` at top\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: `mypy` passes without errors\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Improve error messages with actionable guidance\n  - Include specific error details from DockerException\n  - Add context about what operation failed\n  - Suggest common resolutions where applicable\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Error messages are clear and helpful\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Add validation for build arguments\n  - Check that build_args values are strings\n  - Log warnings for potentially invalid args\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Invalid build args produce warnings\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Add comprehensive logging for verbose mode\n  - Log build args in verbose mode\n  - Log registry URL (not credentials) in verbose mode\n  - Log image tagging operations\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Verbose mode shows detailed operation logs\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Unit Tests\n\n### DockerService Initialization Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Test `__init__` creates Docker client\n  - Mock `docker.from_env`\n  - Verify client is created\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: `_client` is set\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Test `__init__` handles Docker unavailable\n  - Mock `docker.from_env` to raise `DockerException`\n  - Verify `_client` is None\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: No exception raised, graceful degradation\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Test `__init__` verbose mode sets logging\n  - Mock `logging.basicConfig`\n  - Verify DEBUG level set when verbose=True\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: `basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` called\n\n### Docker Availability Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Test `check_docker_available` returns True when running\n  - Mock client ping to succeed\n  - Verify returns True\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Boolean True returned\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Test `check_docker_available` returns False when client None\n  - Set `_client = None`\n  - Verify returns False\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Boolean False returned\n\n- [ ] **T3.6** Test `check_docker_available` returns False when ping fails\n  - Mock client ping to raise `DockerException`\n  - Verify returns False\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Boolean False returned\n\n### Build Image Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.7** Test `build_image` success returns complete dict\n  - Mock `client.images.build`\n  - Create temp Dockerfile\n  - Verify result contains `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: All required fields present\n\n- [ ] **T3.8** Test `build_image` raises when Docker unavailable\n  - Mock `check_docker_available` to return False\n  - Verify `RuntimeError` raised\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Exception with \"Docker is not available\" message\n\n- [ ] **T3.9** Test `build_image` passes build arguments\n  - Mock build, pass build_args dict\n  - Verify buildargs passed to Docker SDK\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Correct build args in call\n\n- [ ] **T3.10** Test `build_image` tracks build time\n  - Mock build with delay\n  - Verify build_time is reasonable\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: build_time > 0\n\n- [ ] **T3.11** Test `build_image` handles APIError\n  - Mock build to raise `APIError`\n  - Verify `RuntimeError` raised with context\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Wrapped exception\n\n### Get Image Info Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.12** Test `get_image_info` success\n  - Mock `client.images.get`\n  - Verify returns dict with all fields\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Correct structure\n\n- [ ] **T3.13** Test `get_image_info` returns empty dict on failure\n  - Mock to raise `DockerException`\n  - Verify returns `{}`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Empty dict returned\n\n- [ ] **T3.14** Test `_format_size` for all units\n  - Test bytes, KB, MB, GB, TB\n  - Verify correct formatting\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: \"500.00 B\", \"1.00 KB\", \"1.00 MB\", etc.\n\n### Push Image Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.15** Test `push_image` success\n  - Mock push with success logs\n  - Verify returns `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Correct structure\n\n- [ ] **T3.16** Test `push_image` with registry tags image\n  - Mock push with registry_url\n  - Verify `_tag_image_sdk` called\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Tag operation performed\n\n- [ ] **T3.17** Test `push_image` with credentials logs in\n  - Mock push with username/password\n  - Verify `_docker_login_sdk` called\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Login performed\n\n- [ ] **T3.18** Test `push_image` raises when Docker unavailable\n  - Mock `check_docker_available` to return False\n  - Verify `RuntimeError` raised\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Exception raised\n\n- [ ] **T3.19** Test `push_image` handles push error in logs\n  - Mock push logs with error entry\n  - Verify `RuntimeError` raised\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Error from logs propagated\n\n### Registry Login Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.20** Test `_docker_login_sdk` success\n  - Mock `client.login`\n  - Verify login called with correct params\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Credentials passed correctly\n\n- [ ] **T3.21** Test `_docker_login_sdk` uses default registry\n  - Call with registry=None\n  - Verify Docker Hub URL used\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Default registry in call\n\n- [ ] **T3.22** Test `_docker_login_sdk` raises on failure\n  - Mock login to raise `APIError`\n  - Verify `RuntimeError` raised\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Wrapped exception\n\n### Tag Image Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.23** Test `_tag_image_sdk` success\n  - Mock `client.images.get` and `image.tag`\n  - Verify tag called with force=True\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Tag operation performed\n\n- [ ] **T3.24** Test `_tag_image_sdk` raises on failure\n  - Mock to raise `DockerException`\n  - Verify `RuntimeError` raised\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Wrapped exception\n\n### Remove Image Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.25** Test `remove_image` success\n  - Mock `client.images.remove`\n  - Verify returns True\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Image removed\n\n- [ ] **T3.26** Test `remove_image` returns False on failure\n  - Mock to raise `DockerException`\n  - Verify returns False\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: No exception, returns False\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Test build-then-push workflow\n  - Create temp Dockerfile\n  - Mock build and push\n  - Verify workflow completes\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: End-to-end workflow works\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Test integration with BuildRuntime\n  - Create BuildRuntime with DockerService\n  - Mock Docker operations\n  - Verify BuildRuntime.build() uses DockerService correctly\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Integration works\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Test integration with PublishRuntime\n  - Create PublishRuntime with DockerService\n  - Mock Docker operations\n  - Verify PublishRuntime uses push correctly\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Integration works\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Add comprehensive docstrings to all methods\n  - Document parameters, returns, raises\n  - Include examples where helpful\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verify: Complete documentation\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Update README with DockerService usage examples\n  - Show how to instantiate DockerService\n  - Show build, push, remove examples\n  - Show error handling patterns\n  - File: `cmd/cli/README.md` or `docs/docker-service.md`\n  - Verify: Examples are runnable\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Document common errors and resolutions\n  - Docker not available\n  - Build failures\n  - Push authentication failures\n  - File: `cmd/cli/README.md` or `docs/docker-service.md`\n  - Verify: Clear troubleshooting guide\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Add type hints documentation\n  - Document all type hints\n  - Explain complex types if needed\n  - File: Code comments or docs\n  - Verify: Types are clear\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Code Quality\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Run mypy type checking\n  - Command: `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Fix all type errors\n  - Verify: No mypy errors\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Run ruff linting\n  - Command: `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Fix all lint errors\n  - Verify: No ruff errors\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Run pytest with coverage\n  - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n  - Verify coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify: All methods tested\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Verify integration with AR-022\n  - Ensure BuildRuntime can use DockerService\n  - Ensure PublishRuntime can use DockerService\n  - Verify: No breaking changes\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `DockerService` class implements all specified methods\n2. ✅ `build_image()` returns complete result dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n3. ✅ `push_image()` returns `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n4. ✅ Verbose mode provides detailed operation logs\n5. ✅ Error messages are actionable and include root cause\n6. ⏳ Unit tests cover all methods and error paths\n7. ⏳ Type hints are present on all public methods\n8. ⏳ Docstrings follow Google/NumPy style conventions\n9. ⏳ Integration with `BuildRuntime` and `PublishRuntime` verified\n10. ⏳ Code coverage >= 80%\n11. ⏳ Documentation includes usage examples and troubleshooting\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Per proposal.md, Stage ST-3 is marked complete: DockerService is implemented\n- Remaining work: enhanced documentation (Phase 2, 5), comprehensive testing (Phase 3, 4), code quality checks (Phas